    <section><title>Useful Tips</title>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    If the packet-forwarding is used to connect workers, than don't forget to add the following to you PROOF script:
                    <programlisting>
                        proof->SetParameter( "PROOF_MaxSlavesPerNode", (Long_t)100 );
                    </programlisting>
                    Otherwise PROOF will not use all workers you actually requested.
                    <ulink url="http://www-linux.gsi.de/%7Emanafov/D-Grid/docz/PoD/html/html_help/Known_Issues.html#MaxSlavesPerNode">Find out more on this.</ulink>
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    Automate your connection string by using the <command>pod-info</command> command:
                    <programlisting>
                        TProof::Open(gSystem->GetFromPipe("pod-info -c"));
                    </programlisting>
                    This is needed, since PoD's automatic port mapping will time to time assign PROOF's server to a different ports. The <command>pod-info</command> command
                    insures you that you always get the current connection string.
                </para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        

        <section><title>PoD at GSI (OGE)</title>
            <para>
                For GSI users, who wants to use PoD with our new OGE cluster. You need to build source package of PoD using the following environment.
            </para>
<screen>
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$SGE_ROOT/lib/$SGE_ARCH/:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
export PATH=/misc/manafov/cmake/cmake_64bit/cmake/bin:$PATH
export PATH=/misc/manafov/Qt/4.4.2_lenny64/bin:$PATH
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/misc/manafov/Qt/4.4.2_lenny64/lib:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
</screen>
        </section>
        
        <section><title>PoD at GSI (LSF)</title>
            <para>
                For GSI users there is a pre-compiled and tuned version of PoD. From the <olink targetdocent="download.xml">Download page</olink> get the tar ball of
                the PoD, which is marked by <emphasis role="bold">"for GSI environment only"</emphasis>. For installation and configuration details please refer
                to user's manual.
            </para>
            <note><para>
                Be advised, that PoD 2.2 requires at least cmake 2.6.2. As you may know GSI environment provides an antic version of cmake, which can't be used.
                In order to instal PoD you need either <ulink url="http://www.cmake.org/cmake/resources/software.html">to install cmake</ulink>
                locally to you home folder (it is very easy and fast process) or just use Anar's pre-compiled cmake by exporting it to your <envar>$PATH</envar> variable.
            </para>
                <para>
                    For 64bit Etch:
<screen>
export PATH=/misc/manafov/cmake/cmake_64bit/cmake/bin:$PATH
</screen>
                    For 32bit Etch:
<screen>
export PATH=/misc/manafov/cmake/cmake_32bit/bin:$PATH
</screen>
                </para></note>
        </section>
        
        <section><title>PoD at CERN's AFS</title>
            <para>
                PoD has been tested and is used at CERN. The following environment settings could help to build PoD from the source in a CERN AFS directory on lxplus.cern.ch.
<screen>
# GCC
. /afs/cern.ch/sw/lcg/contrib/gcc/4.3/x86_64-slc5/setup.sh
# ROOT (you can use your version)
. /afs/cern.ch/sw/lcg/app/releases/ROOT/5.27.06/x86_64-slc5-gcc43-opt/root/bin/thisroot.sh
# Qt
export PATH=/afs/cern.ch/sw/lcg/external/qt/4.4.2/x86_64-slc5-gcc43-opt/bin:$PATH
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/afs/cern.ch/sw/lcg/external/qt/4.4.2/x86_64-slc5-gcc43-opt/lib:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
</screen>
            </para>
            <para>
                Since AFS doesn't support pipes you need to change PoDâ€™s working directory in the user defaults configuration file $POD_LOCATION/etc/PoD.cfg to /tmp/[login name]/ or to something like that:
<programlisting>
[server]
#
# PoD working directory
#
work_dir=/tmp/manafov/
</programlisting>
            </para>
        </section>
